  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Incomes for Farmers in the Maddaben Union</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Training of farmers on improved agricultural production technologies
- Farmers Field Schools
- Radios broadcasts
- Groundnut oil extraction by groups of women
-Seed multipliers training
- Production and distribution of improved seed
- Training of members of the Board of the Marketing union
-Training of members of the Management Committee for stores in storage technology</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers (men and women), Cooperative members</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to improve the quality of life for household members of the Maddaben Union. This goal will be achieved through the following objectives:
 
&#x2022; Objective 1: Increasing and diversifying the production of family farms. 
   o Output 1.1: Farmers apply improved farming techniques. 
   o Output 1.2: Specific needs of women are taken into account. 
&#x2022; Objective 2: The Union is able to deliver quality services to its members. 
  o Output 2.1: High quality dry cereal, legume, and oleaginous seeds are available.
  o Output 2.2: The union masters the technical supply of inputs and marketing channels of agricultural products.
  o Output 2.3: The union has adequate financial and material resources. 
&#x2022; Objective 3: The cooperatives of the union are operational. 
  o Output 3.1: Cooperatives apply principles of good governance. 
  o Output 3.2: Cooperatives have their own financial resources.</narrative>
  </description>
